      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but i already feel super sluggish and the doctors here always just say \"wait and see\" or \"eat more fish\" which isn't really helpful... i've seen a lot of wellness influencers saying that doing a \"loading dose\" of 50k for like 10-14 days is actually a standard way to reset your levels when you're slammed. if i only do it for a couple weeks before dropping back down to a normal dose, it shouldn't really cause any permanent damage or anything, right?",
